Guideline text:

NeonLabs – Brand Guidelines (Summary)

Logo:
- Logo can be used in full color or white.
- White logo preferred on dark or gradient backgrounds.
- Minimum size flexible for digital use.
- Logo can be centered or top-left.
- Avoid placing logo on low-contrast backgrounds.

Colors:
Primary:
- Electric Purple: #7C3AED
- Neon Pink: #FF2D95
Secondary:
- Cyan: #22D3EE
- Dark Background: #0F172A

Color usage:
- Use bold gradients and high contrast.
- Combine purple + pink frequently.
- Cyan used for highlights and interactive elements.

Typography:
- Brand font: Inter
- Office font: Arial
- Use Arial for PowerPoint if Inter unavailable.

Style:
- Bold, modern, high-energy.
- Prefer large titles and strong visual hierarchy.
- Use accent colors frequently.
- Avoid overly dense slides.